description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a fantastic opportunity at Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust for a registered pharmacist to work in our out patient dispensary providing a high quality service to patients who have been seen either in a face to face or a virtual consultation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;COVID 19 has created many challenges to the way in which we deliver out-patient services and you will be involved in supporting a range of innovative developments that are being implemented to keep our patients safe while providing quick and easy access to their medicines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is focused on delivering an efficient and accurate dispensing service to out-patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the Principal Pharmacist, Out Patient Services and Clinical Trials and have the opportunity to develop your management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need excellent interpersonal and communication skills and the ability to organise and prioritise your work and that of others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be involved in the dispensing and management of Clinical Trials and the regular production of KPIs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post includes participation in the late duty, weekend, bank holiday and on-call rotas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSue WrightJob titleDeputy Chief Pharmacist, Operational and Patient ServicesEmail addresssue.wright26@nhs.netTelephone number02082964033 (Mondays and Tuesdays) and 01372 735337 (Wednesdays, Thursdays and Fridays)&lt;/p&gt;
